definition.value: An androstanoid that is testosterone substituted by a alpha-hydroxy group at position 7. A natural product found in Daphnia magna exposed to the biocide tributyltin
Any gamma-lactone having the lactone moiety derived from 4-hydroxybutanoic acid.
A racemate comprising equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-cybenzoxasulfyl. It is an insecticide developed by Nihon Nohyaku Co.
The (R)-enantiomer of cybenzoxasulfyl.
The (S)-enantiomer of cybenzoxasulfyl.
A member of the class of pyrimidines that is pyrimidine substituted by a 2-carboxyethyl group at position 2.
Any  ketone that is butane substituted by an oxo group at unspecified position.
A 1,3-benzoxazole substituted by 5-cyclopropyl-3-(ethylsulfonyl)pyridin-2-yl and (trifluoromethyl)sulfinyl groups at positions 2 and 5, respectively.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphinic acid and the carboxylic acid groups; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An S-substituted L-cysteine where the S-substituent is specified as trisulfanyl.
Major species at pH 7.3.

A phenylalkylamine that is propan-1-amine substituted by a phenyl group at position 2. It is classified as a doping agent by the World Anti-Doping Agency.
A tetracyclic sesquiterpenoid.
The (S)-enantiomer of 2-phenylpropylamine.

A biphenyl that is 1,1'-biphenyl substituted by (4,5-dimethyl-1,2-oxazol-3-yl)aminosulfonyl, ethoxymethyl, and (2-butyl-4-oxo-1,3-diazaspiro[4.4]non-1-en-3-yl)methyl groups at positions 2, 2' and 4', respectively. It is a dual antagonist of endothelin and angiotensin II receptors approved for the reduction of proteinuria in adults with primary immunoglobulin A nephropathy at risk of rapid disease progression.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3 of silphinene-15-oic acid
An alanine derivative that is alanine substituted by a naphthalen-2-yl group at position 3.
A rebaudioside that is steviol in which the hydroxy group is replaced by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->2)-[beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->3)]-beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.
A member of the class of azabicycloalkanes that is (1R,2S,5R)-3-methyl-7-oxo-1,6-diazabicyclo[3.2.1]oct-3-ene-2-carboxamide in which the amino hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a sulfooxy group.
Any short-chain fatty acyl-CoA in which the acyl group specified is butanoyl or its substituted derivative.
